Using GitHub Website
1Go to GitHub and log in.
2Click on the "+" (top-right) → "New repository".
3Enter a repository name and choose Public or Private.
4Click "Create repository" 
5 create a file in repository


Using Git
1Open Git Bash / Terminal
Run these commands:
>>git init
>>git clone linkfromgithub // to use repository in local
Do some modification in the file in local
>> git add . 
>>git commit –m “message”
>>git push
